        "**General rule for one-digit repeats.** $0.\\overline{d} = \\dfrac{d}{9}$ for digit $d$. (Same for $0.\\overline{ab} = \\dfrac{ab}{99}$, $0.\\overline{abc} = \\dfrac{abc}{999}$, etc. — denominator is one 9 per repeating digit.)"
